  "body": "# Issue\r\nThe current presentation of the \"surround\" slashing condition is super hard parse both for implementation and just general understanding. The `+1` and the stringing together of conditionals throws off the intuition behind the condition.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nvotes_1.data.justified_slot + 1 < votes_2.data.justified_slot + 1 == votes_2.data.slot < votes_1.data.slot\r\n```\r\n\r\nI suggest we restate as the following. A little more verbose and a little less clever but much easier to understand.\r\n```python\r\n(votes_1.data.justified_slot < votes_2.data.justified_slot) and\r\n(votes_2.data.justified_slot + 1 == votes_2.data.slot) and\r\n(votes_2.data.slot < votes_1.data.slot)\r\n```\r\nThis more clearly shows that we are slashing when a vote entirely surrounds another vote that could result in finality.\r\n\r\n\r\n[also define `votes_1` and `votes_2` as vars to reduce the clutter of putting `casper_slashing` everywhere]",
